Menu="power.optimizer:10"
Title="Home"
---
<div class="home-wrap">
    <h2>Unraid Power Optimizer</h2>

    <p>
        The overall goal of this plugin is to reduce system power consumption while preserving expected day-to-day behavior.
        Sane defaults are provided for each section, and optimizations are applied with a best-effort approach to avoid system instability.
        However, this plug-in cannot gaurantee perfect operation since hardware and firmware behavior vary between systems.
    </p>

    <hr>

    <div class="home-grid">
        <div class="home-card">
            <h3>PCI Express</h3>
            <p>ASPM, CLKPM, LTR, L1SS, and runtime PM controls with manual device targeting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="home-card">
            <h3>CPU</h3>
            <p>CPU governor and turbo behavior tuning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="home-card">
            <h3>Ethernet</h3>
            <p>EEE and Wake on LAN controls with optional manual interface selection.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="home-card">
            <h3>Disks and USB</h3>
            <p>SATA link power management and autosuspend/runtime PM settings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="home-card">
            <h3>I2C</h3>
            <p>Dedicated I2C runtime PM controls with manual target and device glob support.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="home-card">
            <h3>System Tunables</h3>
            <p>System-level tunables for audio codec PM, scheduler, and watchdog controls.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
.home-wrap {
    max-width: 1100px;
}

.home-grid {
    margin-top: 12px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 12px;
}

.home-card {
    border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 10px;
    background: #f8fafc;
    color: #111827;
}

.home-card h3 {
    margin: 0 0 8px;
}

.home-card p {
    margin: 0;
}
</style>
